textDelta: Where is real power located in the United Nations? The Security Council has the primary responsibility for the maintenance of international peace and security.
Where is the wavelength found in electromagnetic radiation? The wavelength is found in electromagnetic radiation by measuring the distance between two consecutive peaks in the wave.
What region of the spectrum is the wavelength found in electromagnetic radiation? The wavelength in electromagnetic radiation is found in the visible region of the spectrum.
more dietary protein could improve health In a study of over 7,000 people, those who ate more protein were more likely to have better health outcomes, including a reduced risk of death.

more dietary protein may lead to weight gain There is no evidence that eating more dietary protein leads to weight gain. In fact, several studies have shown that high-protein diets may help with weight loss or maintenance.

additional dietary protein may be necessary to maintain muscle mass during weight loss). Athletes who restrict their caloric intake to lose weight may need to consume more protein to maintain muscle mass.
what basic skeletal functions does muscle tissue provide Muscle tissue provides movement and support to the body.
What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the muscle fiber.
